  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing The Server Framework**\n\nOkay, I\'m now actively focusing on building the `/server.ts` file. My goal is to create a robust Express server. I\'m prioritizing implementing authentic, secure REST APIs within the server structure. I\'m now evaluating various database models to determine the most effective representation.\n\n\n**Refining The Database Engine**\n\nI\'ve decided to embed a lightweight, JSON-file-based database directly within `/server.ts` or `server/database/db.ts` to keep the project modular, making the code clean and easily readable/editable. I\'m focusing on the modular backend route files now, or adding the routes directly into `/server.ts`. I have decided to keep everything within `/server.ts` to ensure easy compilation and execution, along with proper `bcryptjs` for password hashing and `jsonwebtoken` for token management. I will define the in-memory/JSON-file collections: `users`, `bookings`, and `otps`.\n\n\n**Defining API Route Structure**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in outlining the API endpoints. I\'m actively working on the `user authentication` module with routes for registration, login, OTP verification, password reset, and user profile retrieval. I\'m focusing on JWT creation/verification and ensuring secure password hashing with bcrypt. Following that, I\'ll be working on the Booking API structure. I\'m thinking of how the booking object should be structured, and how it will interact with the User object.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now create `/server.ts`, which serves as our production-grade full-stack Express.js gateway. It integrates Vite as a dev middleware, hashes passwords with `bcryptjs`, manages secure JWT authentication payloads, and operates an automated JSON-file storage system for users, sessions, and active bookings, ensuring the platform runs immediately in our preview sandbox."
    thinking_duration {
